744 /******************** Bits definition for ADC_ISR register ******************/
745 #define ADC_ISR_ADRDY_Pos (0U)
746 #define ADC_ISR_ADRDY_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_ADRDY_Pos)
747 #define ADC_ISR_ADRDY ADC_ISR_ADRDY_Msk
748 #define ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Pos (1U)
749 #define ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Pos)
750 #define ADC_ISR_EOSMP ADC_ISR_EOSMP_Msk
751 #define ADC_ISR_EOC_Pos (2U)
752 #define ADC_ISR_EOC_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_EOC_Pos)
753 #define ADC_ISR_EOC ADC_ISR_EOC_Msk
754 #define ADC_ISR_EOS_Pos (3U)
755 #define ADC_ISR_EOS_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_EOS_Pos)
756 #define ADC_ISR_EOS ADC_ISR_EOS_Msk
757 #define ADC_ISR_OVR_Pos (4U)
758 #define ADC_ISR_OVR_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_OVR_Pos)
759 #define ADC_ISR_OVR ADC_ISR_OVR_Msk
760 #define ADC_ISR_AWD1_Pos (7U)
761 #define ADC_ISR_AWD1_Msk (0x1U << ADC_ISR_AWD1_Pos)
762 #define ADC_ISR_AWD1 ADC_ISR_AWD1_Msk
764 /* Legacy defines */
765 #define ADC_ISR_AWD (ADC_ISR_AWD1)
766 #define ADC_ISR_EOSEQ (ADC_ISR_EOS)

770 #define ADC_IER_ADRDYIE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_ADRDYIE_Pos)
771 #define ADC_IER_ADRDYIE ADC_IER_ADRDYIE_Msk
772 #define ADC_IER_EOSMPIE_Pos (1U)
773 #define ADC_IER_EOSMPIE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_EOSMPIE_Pos)
774 #define ADC_IER_EOSMPIE ADC_IER_EOSMPIE_Msk
775 #define ADC_IER_EOCIE_Pos (2U)
776 #define ADC_IER_EOCIE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_EOCIE_Pos)
777 #define ADC_IER_EOCIE ADC_IER_EOCIE_Msk
778 #define ADC_IER_EOSIE_Pos (3U)
779 #define ADC_IER_EOSIE_Msk (0x1U << ADC_IER_EOSIE_Pos)
780 #define ADC_IER_EOSIE ADC_IER_EOSIE_Msk

10582 /******************************************************************************/
10583 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F0xx device product */
10584 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
10585 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
10586 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
10587 /* product lines within the same STM32F0 Family */
10588 /******************************************************************************/
10589 
10590 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
10591 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQn ADC1_IRQn
10592 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQn DMA1_Channel1_IRQn
10593 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQn DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQn
10594 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
10595 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
10596 #define PVD_IRQn PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn
10597 #define VDDIO2_IRQn PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn
10598 #define RCC_IRQn RCC_CRS_IRQn
10599 
10600 
10601 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
10602 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQHandler ADC1_IRQHandler
10603 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel1_IRQHandler
10604 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQHandler
10605 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
10606 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
10607 #define PVD_IRQHandler PVD_VDDIO2_IRQHandler
10608 #define VDDIO2_IRQHandler PVD_VDDIO2_IRQHandler
10609 #define RCC_IRQHandler RCC_CRS_IRQHandler
10610 
10611 
10612 #ifdef __cplusplus
10613 }
10614 #endif /* __cplusplus */
10615
